{
  "stem": "15962.4",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "In that-- in that position, I was able, a number of times, to go to camps which had people who just arrived.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And on such occasion, a man who lived in our town-- several men were there-- and I was able to bring them some soup.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "One of these men, later on, became my guardian after the war.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 10 SECONDS] We-- we were placed together for the-- for several months in this block, which half of it was for a punishment cell.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And we had to hear and, sometimes, see horrible torture of human beings.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Particular memory are the prisoners who tried to escape and who were brought back and slowly killed by [BACKROUND NOISE] horrible beating and other punishment.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And then, when they were-- you know-- 90% dead, they were publicly hanged.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And everybody had to come and witness the hanging.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Public beatings were often a mandatory spectacle as well.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And the neighboring block had this-- what was called a special commando, Sonderkommando, which worked in the gas chambers.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And they would, in a way, have a privileged position, because they could steal cigarettes and food from the freshly-arrived people or sometimes even gold teeth that they exchanged for food with the SS and did all sorts of business.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "On the other hand, they knew that every few months they themselves would be driven into the gas chamber, so that they could not tell what they saw to the next generation, so to the next group.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "So it was-- you know-- like, knowing to be on death-row and performing horrible tasks.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
